commit_message:
Devstack: Use [deploy] erase_devices_priority config option

The configuration option [agent] agent_erase_devices_priority was
deprecated and renamed to [deploy] erase_devices_priority as part of the
commit 9a35ca19b4872af2e02cb83b21a3746732802e74.

This patch also fixes the FIXME comment because it's wrong, cleaning is
not disabled in gate, only the erase_devices step.

Change-Id: Iae25a5c672896af77fdd2005371d2515aabaa830

commit_message:
Make restore-cluster.sh use VBM_EXE instead of vboxmanage

On OS X, "vboxmanage" works only if the file system is not
case-sensitive, because the file is called VBoxManage (on Linux,
VirtualBox installs an additional link named vboxmanage).

Change-Id: I3d72b2736bc38d17127627fd1918fc19eb239f58

commit_message:
Fix iniset_no_section

The iniset_no_section function replaces strings if the option name
occurs anywhere in a line of the configuration file. That includes
options that are commented out and even completely unrelated lines that
just happen to contain an option name somewhere.

This patch uses the same logic as functions-common-devstack from which
the function was copied to begin with.

Change-Id: I32dae18173b2b0ca27ba144a19ddf535ced4ba21

commit_message:
Variable ostype for VirtualBox VMs

Until now, osbash always used ostype Ubuntu_64. This patch turns the
value into a variable, letting the VirtualBox GUI display the proper
icon for node operating systems other than Ubuntu.

Change-Id: I416da17226d7513dbb65c76edb55c76d7213a161

subject: Wait for heat test stack to disappear
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-05 03:18:41.000000000', 'files': ['labs/osbash/scripts/ubuntu/setup_heat_network.sh'], 'message': 'Wait for heat test stack to disappear

Right after setup_heat_network.sh deletes the test stack, we shut down
the controller node for a snapshot. This opens a race: the controller
node may never actually delete the heat stack. The test stack stays
in the system, using up the space the test script, launch_instance.sh
needs for its instance VM.

With this patch, setup_heat_network.sh waits for the test stack to
disappear.

Change-Id: I23241998a40b904ef9c26717619e66d4377ce6f9
'}]
commit_message:
Wait for heat test stack to disappear

Right after setup_heat_network.sh deletes the test stack, we shut down
the controller node for a snapshot. This opens a race: the controller
node may never actually delete the heat stack. The test stack stays
in the system, using up the space the test script, launch_instance.sh
needs for its instance VM.

With this patch, setup_heat_network.sh waits for the test stack to
disappear.

Change-Id: I23241998a40b904ef9c26717619e66d4377ce6f9

[{'number': 12, 'created': '2015-12-09 15:01:59.000000000', 'files': ['nova/pci/devspec.py', 'nova/pci/utils.py', 'nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/pci/test_utils.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': 'libvirt: report pci Type-PF type even when VFs are disabled

libvirt < 1.3 reports virt_functions capability only when pf has
VFs enabled. This workaround patch updates the is_physical_function
function to read the sriov_totalvfs if exists and check it is
greater than 0. The sriov_totalvfs is the number for the
maximum possible VF for this PF. _get_pcidev_info in libvirt driver
is updated to get the correct pci device type using this function.

Closes-Bug: #1499204

'}]
commit_message:
libvirt: report pci Type-PF type even when VFs are disabled

libvirt < 1.3 reports virt_functions capability only when pf has
VFs enabled. This workaround patch updates the is_physical_function
function to read the sriov_totalvfs if exists and check it is
greater than 0. The sriov_totalvfs is the number for the
maximum possible VF for this PF. _get_pcidev_info in libvirt driver
is updated to get the correct pci device type using this function.

Closes-Bug: #1499204
Change-Id: I8990c36fb1d6c66093a465930ff3f0948dd64986

commit_message:
Align some defaults with with ControllerCount default

NeutronDhcpAgentsPerNetwork is normally correlated with the
number of controllers, so given that the template
defaults the ControllerCount to 1, 1 seems like a more consistent
value for NeutronDhcpAgentsPerNetwork, and it's consistent with
what we test in CI.

Also NeutronL3HA defaults to False, which is consistent with the default
ControllerCount of 1, but NeutronAllowL3AgentFailover defaults to
True, which I assume makes no sense if there's only 1 controller
and no HA

Change-Id: I4612060979d1e4381800f30e359f58aeef61b861
(cherry picked from commit 1029b994d1b5e0c641da97886f75d982eb2c10f0)

commit_message:
Allow a user to specify a comma separated list of ntp servers

just one.

commit_message:
Remove py26 support

As of Mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. since we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.
Closes-Bug: 1519510

Change-Id: Ifc92fdb0823a032d9b9f744494276a702a16e8b7

commit_message:
ML2: Add tests to validate quota usage tracking

Ensure that event handlers are invoked upon completion of
ML2 operations which add or remove tracked resources.
Also validate that the event handlers are called for the
appropriate resources and that quota usage's dirty bit
is set and unset as expected.

These are not unit tests, but added in the unit test tree
as they leverage code both from the DB unit test and the ML2
unit test framework. This module has indeed been added to
the 'exclusion list' in check_unit_test_structure.sh, and
should be moved to the functional test tree together with
the other modules.

Conflicts:
	neutron/quota/resource.py

Closes-Bug: #1499358

Change-Id: I78c432c35f3f3339607cd533019ae6d0fa2a5cd6
(cherry picked from commit cdd049e4c4d7e6ba1ca377e50fc6e8c29c85ab3d)

commit_message:
vmware: Drop JSON for supported_instances

The virt drivers pass the value for supported_instances
to the resource tracker as a JSON encoded string. This
gets decoded as soon as it is copied to the compute node
object. The JSON is not used anymore since compute node
object was added so we will remove the encoding for all
virt drivers.

This patch removes that unnecessary encoding from the
vmware driver.

blueprint mitaka-objects

Change-Id: I0680fd236e607a9ea0909f596d31033c3600c494

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: I932a82be1e0f88bb1e333a9a7c3fc5bf87fa9e79

commit_message:
Normalize server objects

There are a set of things we always want to do to server dicts because
they are no-cost. This is in line with how we manage other resource
dicts, so make a normalize function. However, because we need to add
cloud and region info from the cloud object, make it a member method
rather than an friend function. Then, ensure it's always called on
server related calls.

Change-Id: Ied869efcb7d83c4f1a753962ca3127ce52172a24

commit_message:
Instance Caching

This is the work to complete the resource-metadata-caching blueprint.

* Implement an in-memory cache in the compute agent.
* Change compute-agent to populate an in-memory cache.
* Change compute-agent to use the changes-since parameter in the Nova API call .
* Change compute-agent to record the polling timestamp in the cache.
* Change compute-agent to cache the flavor and image metadata as well.

Implements blueprint resource-metadata-caching

Change-Id: I97594e082db6d8e34d9201a7ec5710978e557d6d
Signed-off-by: Jason Myers <jason@jasonamyers.com>

commit_message:
Make restore-cluster.sh use VBM_EXE instead of vboxmanage

On OS X, "vboxmanage" works only if the file system is not
case-sensitive, because the file is called VBoxManage (on Linux,
VirtualBox installs an additional link named vboxmanage).

Change-Id: I3d72b2736bc38d17127627fd1918fc19eb239f58

commit_message:
Fix iniset_no_section

The iniset_no_section function replaces strings if the option name
occurs anywhere in a line of the configuration file. That includes
options that are commented out and even completely unrelated lines that
just happen to contain an option name somewhere.

This patch uses the same logic as functions-common-devstack from which
the function was copied to begin with.

Change-Id: I32dae18173b2b0ca27ba144a19ddf535ced4ba21

subject: Wait for heat test stack to disappear
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-02 07:27:22.000000000', 'files': ['labs/osbash/scripts/ubuntu/setup_heat_network.sh'], 'message': 'Wait for heat test stack to disappear

Right after setup_heat_network.sh deletes the test stack, we shut down
the controller node for a snapshot. This opens a race: the controller
node may never actually delete the heat stack. The test stack stays
in the system, using up the space the test script, launch_instance.sh
needs for its instance VM.

With this patch, setup_heat_network.sh waits for the test stack to
disappear.

Change-Id: I23241998a40b904ef9c26717619e66d4377ce6f9
'}]
commit_message:
Wait for heat test stack to disappear

Right after setup_heat_network.sh deletes the test stack, we shut down
the controller node for a snapshot. This opens a race: the controller
node may never actually delete the heat stack. The test stack stays
in the system, using up the space the test script, launch_instance.sh
needs for its instance VM.

With this patch, setup_heat_network.sh waits for the test stack to
disappear.

Change-Id: I23241998a40b904ef9c26717619e66d4377ce6f9

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-24 14:05:55.000000000', 'files': ['manifests/storage/all.pp', 'spec/defines/swift_storage_server_spec.rb', 'spec/classes/swift_storage_all_spec.rb', 'manifests/storage/server.pp'], 'message': 'Change defaults fro incoming/outgoing chmod (rsync)

In a previous release, we sent a warning about the default
incoming/outgoing chmod that was configured for rsync.
We mentionned it was risky and people should avoid using 0644 like it
was by default. For backward compatibility, we kept this default and
sent a warning.

2 releases later, this patch aims to change the default and stop to send

Change-Id: Ic3aaaec0eee4225bf2021937edf972528ea72e2c

'}]
commit_message:
Change defaults fro incoming/outgoing chmod (rsync)

In a previous release, we sent a warning about the default
incoming/outgoing chmod that was configured for rsync.
We mentionned it was risky and people should avoid using 0644 like it
was by default. For backward compatibility, we kept this default and
sent a warning.

2 releases later, this patch aims to change the default and stop to send
the warning.

Change-Id: Ic3aaaec0eee4225bf2021937edf972528ea72e2c
Closes-bug: #1433390

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-23 22:47:56.000000000', 'files': ['spec/classes/nova_api_spec.rb', 'spec/classes/nova_keystone_auth_spec.rb', 'manifests/api.pp', 'manifests/init.pp', 'spec/classes/nova_init_spec.rb', 'manifests/keystone/auth.pp', 'spec/acceptance/basic_nova_spec.rb'], 'message': 'Remove EC2 support

EC2 has been dropped in Mitaka [1].
This patch:
* deprecates all ec2 related parameters and have no effect.
* all configuration related to ec2 is dropped.
* all keystone resources related to ec2 are not managed anymore.
* drops acceptance test for ec2 service binding.

This is a backwards-incompatible change for people who were still
deploying ec2 with Nova, but EC2 API has been deprecated for a while
(Juno).

commit_message:
Remove EC2 support

EC2 has been dropped in Mitaka [1].
This patch:
* deprecates all ec2 related parameters and have no effect.
* all configuration related to ec2 is dropped.
* all keystone resources related to ec2 are not managed anymore.
* drops acceptance test for ec2 service binding.

This is a backwards-incompatible change for people who were still
deploying ec2 with Nova, but EC2 API has been deprecated for a while
(Juno).

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/commit/eec7a55319b3f22949735227199ce49b851519b8
Closes-Bug: #1528948

Change-Id: Ie144202648f1aae36cdca9bab5d986ae6c4d3069

commit_message:
Don't return tracebacks in API response in debug mode

The API should not return tracebacks in a production environment. As
deployers often run services in debug mode, because OpenStack is hard to
debug, we should not return tracebacks in debug mode. To allow
developers etc to continue to use this feature, add a new config option
'debug_tracebacks_in_api' that maintains this behavior.

Also add to troubleshooting docs.

Change-Id: Idbbf7efc45140e9e3d8b9491edd58905cbba0363
Closes-Bug: #1525002

commit_message:
Remove requirement of specifying hardware stats

With introspection in place, there is no longer a hard requirement of
knowing the hardware statistics (cpu, memory, disk, arch) of nodes when
initially registering them with Ironic.

The requirement was never on the Ironic side, it was only enforced here
in os-cloud-config. Previously, to get around the requirement, one could
just specify an empty string value for these statistics in the nodes
json file.

This change makes it such that these keys do not even have to exist in
the json anymore.

Add a unit test as well that verifies this change.

Change-Id: Idcc5a9a4ac043c88fe0102626eefb327476819fd

commit_message:
Add Zapping states to node and API

Add ZAPPING, ZAPWAIT, and ZAPFAIL to the state machine, along with the
zap verb. Expose node.zap_step in the API. Allowing 'zap' as a verb
in the API and handling for zapping will come in a second patch.

Bump API version to 1.13 and Node version to 1.14.

Implements: blueprint implement-zapping-states

Change-Id: I4cbc0a54e5ad3aeed230f275d9a7e88a2568d845

commit_message:

Modify the cleaning flow to allow zapping as well. Add a do_node_zap
function to be the target of provisioning actions with target 'zap'.

be shared with do_node_clean and do_node_zap.

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-17 23:05:58.000000000', 'files': ['tools/generate_subunit.py'], 'message': "Add script to create a subunit streams

This commit adds a generate_subunit.py script which is used to
generate a subunit stream with a single result for a period of time.
It takes it 2 mandatory args and 2 optional to specify the start time,
stop time, and optionally the status (it defaults to sucecss) and an id
for test (if one isn't provided 'devstack' is used) The resulting stream
is written to STDOUT.

The intent here is to leverage this to inject 'test results' into the
subunit2sql db to reflect failures that occur before tempest (or any
other test suite) is run. This is necessary for the openstack-health
dashboard. (otherwise it makes our failure rate look much better than
it is) This is only needed until we get a zuul mysql reporter in place
which can give us the higher level run information.

Change-Id: I6bce2c76bbf85ea558a12ba673455332a862a4f9
"}]
commit_message:
Add script to create a subunit streams

This commit adds a generate_subunit.py script which is used to
generate a subunit stream with a single result for a period of time.
It takes it 2 mandatory args and 2 optional to specify the start time,
stop time, and optionally the status (it defaults to sucecss) and an id
for test (if one isn't provided 'devstack' is used) The resulting stream
is written to STDOUT.

The intent here is to leverage this to inject 'test results' into the
subunit2sql db to reflect failures that occur before tempest (or any
other test suite) is run. This is necessary for the openstack-health
dashboard. (otherwise it makes our failure rate look much better than
it is) This is only needed until we get a zuul mysql reporter in place
which can give us the higher level run information.

Change-Id: I6bce2c76bbf85ea558a12ba673455332a862a4f9

commit_message:
Fix v1 image-list doesn't honour --is-public

The issue is different for different roles. For admin role, they
can't list only public images. For non admin role, the filter
is-public is totally skipped now. This patch fixes the two issues
and adds some test cases for that.

Clonses-Bug: #1455311

Change-Id: I76816fd495ca38a5b5433f4081c0b22c3f7544e5

commit_message:
Fix direction problem for sec-group rules with remote_ip_prefix

For ingress rules, remote_ip_prefix should match the source IP,
but current implementation matches destination always. This patch
fix the problem.

Change-Id: I3fad6024d24aaff31447ca73d35a9ab24f122013
Closes-bug: 1530620

commit_message:
Final decomposition of Brocade vendor code

neutron tree. All the vendor code is now in the
openstack/networking-brocade repo.

Closes-Bug: #1518637

commit_message:
Add support to list all security group rules

Both nova and neutron allow security group rules to be listed without
specifying the owning security group. This patch set makes the
group argument on 'os security group rule list' optional. Behavior
is unchanged when the argument is specified. When the argument is
not specified then all accessible security group rules will be listed.
The listing will include the owning security group for each rule.

Change-Id: I6914baecf70a65354e1e82dad92c6afbd32b4973
Related-Bug: #1519512

commit_message:
Add protocol value options to sg-rule-create

This patch will show choices of allowed protocols for security group
rule create and also indicate type and code in help when protocol is
ICMP.

DocImpact

'[0-255]' values are allowed for protocol but not listed anywhere in
description for creating security group rule.

Closes-Bug: #1523063

commit_message:
take_over() for iscsi_ilo doesnt recreate boot iso

When using web server for hosting images for ilo driver,
take_over should recreate the boot ISO, if it was created
by Ironic. If the boot iso is not recreated, then the
node doesn't boot up successfully when a node is powered off
and powered on.

The fix is available in master branch via
I5481e705892f66cb3184ac16ff56c123f5c69087 in file boot.py
from lines 117 to 122. The test case for the fix is available via
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/239627 in master branch.
The master branch patch I5481e705892f66cb3184ac16ff56c123f5c69087
implements a feature (~2K lines of change) while the fix for this
issue is just 5-6 lines of change.

Closes-bug: #1510425

Change-Id: I6b7f3901f773a5aba906c50dcbd574412f7b6af3

commit_message:
Refactor objects into a magic registry

This adds a register hook to the objects base class that allows us to
late-import objects classes into ironic.objects. This is useful to allow
object classes to depend on other objects.

For example, this will allow us to do the Port.node_uuid munging that we
currently do in the API layer, in the objects layer instead.

This is completely taken from Nova, much thanks to comstud and dansmith
and whoever else worked on that.

Change-Id: Ic655e7af533497bda5e8e72d3bd90c27394681a7

commit_message:
Use _i18n instead of i18n

It is suggested to use _i18n.py per oslo.i18n document.
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/usage.html

neutronclient.i18n is now a wrapper module which emits
the derecation warning. It is because might be used in
implementation of the client extensions in other repositories.

Closes-Bug: #1519493
Change-Id: I44969daeedc9a66dd9ad5bf80617516faf245ecc

commit_message:
Require swift package installation before swift user.

- The user 'swift' is being ensured without any restriction on openstack-swift
package, so it is highly potential that the user is created before package is
installed with /bin/bash instead of /sbin/nologin as shell.

Closes-bug: #1525243
Change-Id: I4c7b7afb7eefeda0379db631f14eb8c32cbe8671
Signed-off-by: Gael Chamoulaud <gchamoul@redhat.com>

  of "L3 HA to Legacy".

commit_message:
[networking] Correct enable_dhcp description in IPv6 section

enable_dhcp is not a config option in neutron.conf.
It is an attribute of neutron subnet object.

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-04 14:50:37.000000000', 'files': ['fuel_health/tests/configuration/test_configuration.py'], 'message': "use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I40005893926d3c9e63e0e25fbc8a1dfaa7df80c2
"}]
commit_message:
use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I40005893926d3c9e63e0e25fbc8a1dfaa7df80c2

commit_message:
Remove inaccurate OSI Model reference

Updates to remove calling packets equal to frames. The OSI Model has them at
two different layers and thus this reference was inaccurate.

Closes-Bug: #1515552

Change-Id: Ia828e3e8d8100a878b6e41ba4f80a24bf5e7d589
(cherry picked from commit 4f7e372302bf96d3549799f3b24a3273f8fb372b)

commit_message:
[networking] Fix description of IPv6 RA flag for SLAAC

* Moves "Managed" to the next line. "Managed Configuration Flag"
  is one of the valid RA flags.
* Move "New or existing" to the beginning of the next paragraph.
  The meaning of the next sentence is still correct even after moving
  this. It is still true as IPv6 attributes of neutron subnet can
  be updated.

commit_message:
Change  LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Closes-Bug: #1530742
Change-Id: I9f9f303d7482d0ecc44461bab5ed8f92926436f4

commit_message:
Added CORS support to Cue

This adds the CORS support middleware to Cue, allowing a deployer
to optionally configure rules under which a javascript client may
break the single-origin policy and access the API directly.

For cue, the middleware was added directly to the application
factory, including various default headers usually required by
keystone. Note that the CORS middleware must be the first one in
the middleware chain, so that it can annotate all responses -
even error responses - generated by other middleware.

oslo_config initialization was added to the functional test
initialization, in order to ensure that a fully initialized
config instance is available during tests.

OpenStack CrossProject Spec:
   http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/openstack-specs/specs/cors-support.html
Oslo_Middleware Docs:
   http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.middleware/cors.html
OpenStack Cloud Admin Guide:
   http://docs.openstack.org/admin-guide-cloud/cross_project_cors.html

Change-Id: I7ff60a96f545ff991de06073a80a5750512ebd31

commit_message:
Add tagging fuctionality for heat stacks

Heat provides tagging fuctionality for stacks, now tagging is
possible for stacks generated via murano also. To implement it,
added new config parameter `stack_tags` with default value 'murano'
and tagged heat stacks created during environment deployment with
`stack_tags` parameter's value.

Change-Id: Ib3f4027b78616c02cf3bbb210578df23d7e536d3
Implements: blueprint tag-murano-heat-stacks

commit_message:
Replace unicode with six.text_type

The Unicode type is 'unicode' in Python 2 and 'str' on Python 3.
This patch replaces unicode with six.text_type to make Murano
more compatible with Python 3. Also it replaces the tuple
'(str, unicode)' with six.string_types for instance comparision.

Blueprint murano-python-3-support

Change-Id: I4db27afdb556ec30dd36d7d4e170055274edfa8b

commit_message:
The mirror for installing epel is timing out

Fedora has changed the location of epel, shorting the link
from 'download.fedoraproject.org' to 'dl.fedoraproject.org'.
This change updates the epel mirror to prevent it from timing
out.

Change-Id: I87090282a2f5f757495daec6ad14123b436b1aa0

commit_message:
tripleo.sh add option to delete overcloud

One thing we're lacking CI coverage of atm is deleting an overcloud
and proving the delete actually works, which is proving unreliable
for some users.  First step to fixing that is having tripleo.sh
support deleting an overcloud via heat, then polling until it's
done.

Conflicts:
   scripts/tripleo.sh

Change-Id: If2e1777ec4363788c0df401c3bb470254ca78a33
(cherry picked from commit f9a0219d4308030d2970b5a23b57b1fc9901ddd7)

commit_message:

commit_message:
Moving rsyslog to librarian v2

This change moves the rsyslog module to librarian. This change also
updates the rsyslog module to v3.5.1 from our customized 1.1.4 version.
With the update, our usage of file resources to manage syslog
configuration files has also been updated to leverage the
rsyslog::snippet resource.

This change also cleans up the lint issues with the openstack::logging
class.

The previous version of this patch was reverted due to missed
configuration changes between how 1.1.4 managed rules and how 3.5.1
manages rules. The newer configurations use rulesets for the remote
rules and so the configuration file for the master's rsyslog needs to
target the remote ruleset for where to place remote files.

Partial blueprint: fuel-puppet-librarian

Change-Id: I345844d44545381f0d79b6113eb2dbcc515d77cb

subject: Make the tests page useful
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-22 23:43:45.000000000', 'files': ['test/unit/controllers/tests_spec.js', 'app/js/controllers/tests.js', 'app/views/tests.html'], 'message': "Make the tests page useful

This commit attempts to fix the tests page and make it useful. The
first thing it does is to remove all the bar graphs. These were added
to try and show something visual on the page. But they didn't convey
any information to the user and instead confused people.

The second thing this does is change the grouping to be more logical.
Instead of grouping on the test classes (which was also incorrect and
making assumptions about the path depth) this groups by the top level
path which will be the package the tests were in. (ie like tempest,
manila_tempest, etc) This makes more sense and also future proofs the
dashboard for when non-tempest tests are in the subunit2sql db.

The third thing this patch does is to change the default sorting order
on the tables to put the highest failure percentage at the top. This
will mean that what most people are interested in will be at the top
of the list. The fourth aspect of this patch is to default the groups
to open instead of closed.

Change-Id: I4426ba951276ef5d9482d67d5dfca7cd3d46d800
"}]
commit_message:
Make the tests page useful

This commit attempts to fix the tests page and make it useful. The
first thing it does is to remove all the bar graphs. These were added
to try and show something visual on the page. But they didn't convey
any information to the user and instead confused people.

The second thing this does is change the grouping to be more logical.
Instead of grouping on the test classes (which was also incorrect and
making assumptions about the path depth) this groups by the top level
path which will be the package the tests were in. (ie like tempest,
manila_tempest, etc) This makes more sense and also future proofs the
dashboard for when non-tempest tests are in the subunit2sql db.

The third thing this patch does is to change the default sorting order
on the tables to put the highest failure percentage at the top. This
will mean that what most people are interested in will be at the top
of the list. The fourth aspect of this patch is to default the groups
to open instead of closed.

Change-Id: I4426ba951276ef5d9482d67d5dfca7cd3d46d800

commit_message:
Don't monitor Cinder Volume LVs for disk util.

The disk utilisation monitoring will monitor cinder volumes if they are
attached to an instance and you run the MaaS play again.

We need to avoid this by ensuring that the model of moniitored disks is
not 'VIRTUAL-DISK'.

Change-Id: I6600e0e3cf8949cde332c1139fe6c9e3b0fa85e8
Closes-Bug: #1524770

subject: VMware: Add support for VVOL datastores
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 170, 'name': 'Mike Perez', 'email': 'thingee@gmail.com', 'username': 'thingee'}, {'_account_id': 1736, 'name': 'Ivan Kolodyazhny', 'email': 'e0ne@e0ne.info', 'username': 'e0ne'}, {'_account_id': 9008, 'name': 'VMware NSX CI', 'username': 'vmwareminesweeper', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 9171, 'name': 'Vipin Balachandran', 'email': 'vipin.bl@gmail.com', 'username': 'vbala'}, {'_account_id': 11904, 'name': 'Sean McGinnis', 'email': 'sean.mcginnis@gmail.com', 'username': 'SeanM'}, {'_account_id': 12491, 'name': 'IBM GPFS CI', 'email': 'rsandeep@in.ibm.com', 'username': 'ibm-gpfs-ci', 'inactive': True, 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}, {'_account_id': 18120, 'name': 'Fujitsu ETERNUS CI', 'email': 'fj-lsoft-eternusci@dl.jp.fujitsu.com', 'username': 'Fujitsu_ETERNUS_CI', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-17 11:34:02.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/vmware/datastore.py', 'cinder/volume/drivers/vmware/vmdk.py', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_vmware_vmdk.py'], 'message': 'VMware: Add support for VVOL datastores

vCenter 6.0 added support for a new type of datastore called VVOL
datastore. A VVOL datastore represents a storage container which
is a logical grouping of virtual volumes in an array that supports
VVOL. A virtual disk in a VVOL datastore corresponds to a virtual
volume in the array. Since VVOL datastores are treated like VMFS
or NFS datastores by vCenter APIs, the changes in the VMDK driver
to support VVOL datastores are minimal.

This patch adds the following changes in the VMDK driver to support
VVOL datastores:

* Add VVOL datastore type to the list of allowed datastore types

* Skip VVOL datastore while creating a volume from a preallocated
glance image because it involves replacing the data file of a
temporary virtual disk with the downloaded preallocated image
which VVOL cannot support.

Implements: blueprint vmdk-vvol-support
Change-Id: I528e4caed616dfd9bd85c7de113024bea6709fc1
'}]
commit_message:
VMware: Add support for VVOL datastores

vCenter 6.0 added support for a new type of datastore called VVOL
datastore. A VVOL datastore represents a storage container which
is a logical grouping of virtual volumes in an array that supports
VVOL. A virtual disk in a VVOL datastore corresponds to a virtual
volume in the array. Since VVOL datastores are treated like VMFS
or NFS datastores by vCenter APIs, the changes in the VMDK driver
to support VVOL datastores are minimal.

This patch adds the following changes in the VMDK driver to support
VVOL datastores:

* Add VVOL datastore type to the list of allowed datastore types

* Skip VVOL datastore while creating a volume from a preallocated
glance image because it involves replacing the data file of a
temporary virtual disk with the downloaded preallocated image
which VVOL cannot support.

Implements: blueprint vmdk-vvol-support
Change-Id: I528e4caed616dfd9bd85c7de113024bea6709fc1

commit_message:
Checking the existence of volume

After some fail or cinder-volume restart we want to try create/delete/resize
volume again. To make it more reliable volume drivers should check if backend
already created a volume. The LVM driver and some of the nfs drivers already
contain private _volume_not_present methods, so in this commit we rename these
and expose them as public check_volume_exists methods and add a similar method
for the RBD driver to check if a volume exists on the storage backend. This
commit also adds an ExistingVD for drivers that implement the check_volume_exists
method.

Partial-Implements: blueprint check-volume-exists
Change-Id: Ice8a14d626ed3d8e3790f95c3c5055ef4bacdb30

subject: Use binary mode when reading files
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-01-04 08:40:59.000000000', 'files': ['bandit/core/node_visitor.py', 'bandit/core/manager.py', 'bandit/core/metrics.py'], 'message': 'Use binary mode when reading files

ast module takes two possible sources: bytestrings with possible "# coding: XXX"
line, or decoded strings without it. This means for common processing
bytestrings should be used instead.

The change shouldn't affect the plugins since the string value access is done
via ast, not lines themselves. The universal line splitting is not required in
the open() call since .splitlines() does it by default.

The change allows bandit to run regardless of the LANG environment variable.

Closes-bug: 1516081
Change-Id: Iea57bf66ea9f13b42e0f4143fa3ede476e2e26d9
'}]
commit_message:
Use binary mode when reading files

ast module takes two possible sources: bytestrings with possible "# coding: XXX"
line, or decoded strings without it. This means for common processing
bytestrings should be used instead.

The change shouldn't affect the plugins since the string value access is done
via ast, not lines themselves. The universal line splitting is not required in
the open() call since .splitlines() does it by default.

The change allows bandit to run regardless of the LANG environment variable.

Closes-bug: 1516081
Change-Id: Iea57bf66ea9f13b42e0f4143fa3ede476e2e26d9

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Iafbe78cdcfac329d3795853fe8cc38e549279375
Closes-Bug: #1530742

commit_message:
Properly show missing data in aggregated runs api response

This commit updates the runs aggregator to fill in the timestamps in
the response for missing data. Previously we were manually resampling
the data but only where there was valid data. This commit adds empty
lists to the response object where there is no data. This should
enable the js to properly represent the missing the data on the graph.

Change-Id: I95e37859783dc5597f8f0fc5e4f5e9ec1443d4f3

commit_message:
Make class action calls use version manifest

This follows the object_backport_versions() change by also making the
class action calls pass a version manifest. This is done in a compatible
way by first trying the new method, and if unsupported, falling back
to the original method.

No tests are changed here specifically to demonstrate that they are
undisturbed by this change. Proper tests are next.

Change-Id: If9a158fbd345b56b26ebbe2a0733db55f4929ea1
(cherry picked from commit fa7b1afb924b3d863d37a9f617e55027382df933)

'}]
commit_message:
Enabling domain lookup for project set v3 command

Currently the domain option for `project set` attempts to set
a new domain that owns the project. This is actually an action
that is denied by keystone server. Instead, the domain option
should be used as a lookup, to find projects that exist in the
non-default domain.

commit_message:
Update volume API default version from v1 to v2

Cinder has deprecated API version v1 since Juno release, and
there is a blueprint to remove v1 API support which is in progress.
We should default to v2 API when it's there.

Closes-Bug: 1467589
Change-Id: I83aef4c681cbe342c445f02436fcd40cf1222f23

commit_message:
WIP: change line charts to histograms

This commit switches the graph time on the home page for total jobs to
be a historical bar chart instead of the line graph we were using
before. This should be a bit more accurate in how it displays the data
as it will properly visualize the sample grouping we do and missing
data. While the line graph gives the illusion of continuity which is
misleading.

Change-Id: I1d25df122b24210302e0a35867622ab5cea32f8d

commit_message:
Ensure default arguments are not mutable

* add hacking check: no_mutable_default_args()
* remove the mutable default arguments "[]" or "{}" when the function
  is defined.

ref: http://docs.python-guide.org/en/latest/writing/gotchas/

Closes-Bug: #1530282
Change-Id: Ice6f7654211b73d7f8bc3ca0e4dfae3dca354397

commit_message:
Update Juno SHA's to the final EOL SHA's

This patch sets the repository SHA's to those of the final EOL tags.

This patch also introduces a cap for oslo.utils to prevent further
tags meant for Kilo from interfering with Juno builds.

commit_message:
Document tripleo.sh

Add documentation on how to use tripleo.sh to tripleo-docs. I think just
an overview will be sufficient. I don't feel like we need to go
overboard here, the script is meant to be developer automation, and self
documenting since it's simple bash. No reason to reproduce the same
commands as documention itself.

commit_message:
Fixed test_shell which can't test microversions>=2.4

Method run_command() gets max and min API verisons
from FakeHTTPClient.get_versions(). That's why max version
which could be tested by run)command is 2.3 (because it's
hardcoded in get_versions()).

get_versions() should return max and min versions from
novaclient.__init__.py

Closes-Bug: #1528527

Change-Id: I489c4714cacb345d3b45d5987113093c038cf151

revisions:
[{'number': 15, 'created': '2015-11-04 16:30:33.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/token/provider.py', 'keystone/token/providers/fernet/token_formatters.py', 'keystone/tests/unit/token/test_provider.py', 'keystone/token/providers/fernet/core.py', 'keystone/tests/unit/token/test_fernet_provider.py', 'tox.ini'], 'message': "Fix fernet padding for python 3

In python 3 it's important to keep track of what variables are
text (six.text_type) vs binary (six.binary_type) when dealing
with inputs as strings calling functions that deal with bytes,
such as base64 functions and crypto functions. I added
documentation to track where things are text vs where they're
binary.

TokenFormatter.restore_padding takes text and returns text,
so it shouldn't be using binary '='.

token.provider.base64_encode should return text, not bytes.

token.provider.random_urlsafe_str should return text, not bytes.

A few other byte/string usages were fixed.

The python unicode doc suggests that code should work with
unicode (six.text_type) internally and only switch to bytes
(six.binary_type) at the edges, so this change is a move in that
direction. See https://docs.python.org/3.5/howto/unicode.html .

bp python3

Change-Id: I0723cd50bbb464c38c9efcf1888e39d14950997b
"}]
commit_message:
Fix fernet padding for python 3

In python 3 it's important to keep track of what variables are
text (six.text_type) vs binary (six.binary_type) when dealing
with inputs as strings calling functions that deal with bytes,
such as base64 functions and crypto functions. I added
documentation to track where things are text vs where they're
binary.

TokenFormatter.restore_padding takes text and returns text,
so it shouldn't be using binary '='.

token.provider.base64_encode should return text, not bytes.

token.provider.random_urlsafe_str should return text, not bytes.

A few other byte/string usages were fixed.

The python unicode doc suggests that code should work with
unicode (six.text_type) internally and only switch to bytes
(six.binary_type) at the edges, so this change is a move in that
direction. See https://docs.python.org/3.5/howto/unicode.html .

bp python3

Change-Id: I0723cd50bbb464c38c9efcf1888e39d14950997b

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-04 14:00:13.000000000', 'files': ['doc/install-guide/source/neutron-compute-install.rst'], 'message': "Remove some useless configuration command

A symbolic link which is /etc/neutron/plugin.ini pointing to

compute node.
But it's no need to be created, because there is no

the ML2 plug-in is installed in the controller node.
Thus we should remove this command and skip this step.

Close-bug: #1525075
(cherry picked from commit 76e5f6859b1e99fffe39f917f253da0a5ac67912)
"}]
commit_message:
Remove some useless configuration command

A symbolic link which is /etc/neutron/plugin.ini pointing to
/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini is told to create when
we install and configure the networking service in the
compute node.
But it's no need to be created, because there is no
'/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini' file and
the ML2 plug-in is installed in the controller node.
Thus we should remove this command and skip this step.
Backport: Liberty

Change-Id: I76feb15477ffd2d65cc8eb46c7472b6de830105f
Close-bug: #1525075
(cherry picked from commit 76e5f6859b1e99fffe39f917f253da0a5ac67912)

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Ic19e8cb8cc7c6211f716376e35f5d2d7c68464ef
Closes-Bug: 1530742

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: I10460a02cec125fd8cd34f78e57746b7f55bb172
Closes-Bug: #1530742

commit_message:
[contributor] Rewrite git and git-review on Windows

Installing git and git-review is not prerequisites,
just "set up git and git-review" itself.
To simplify the document structure,
move Windows related contents to the proper section.

* Move "installing git" to "set up git"
* Remove curl and tar or 7-zip as prerequisites
  - they are not needed to install git-review with pip
* Change Python version 2.7 to 3

Change-Id: I1ba39feedb6529b6ba08cd06860393fd926bdaa5
Closes-Bug: #1511943

commit_message:
use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I40005893926d3c9e63e0e25fbc8a1dfaa7df80c2

commit_message:
Add 'use_standard_locale' parameter to execute()

Add 'use_standard_locale' parameter to execute() function.
It defaults to False. If set to True, execute the command
with standard (C) locale added to the environment variables.

Change-Id: I38d0c5feec3f201a0b2775f4df0d1813dfa03d84
Closes-Bug: #1514584

commit_message:
Add support for external load-balancers

Add new hiera configuration key 'external_lb'. If it's set to
true then we should not configure Haproxy LB on controllers and
also we should switch 'haproxy_backend_status' to 'http' provider.

We calculate 'external_lb' during 'globals.pp' task - if we have
no VIPs with 'haproxy' namespace, then it's set to 'true'.

It does not change the default deployment scheme.

Also fixing minor issue with default provider for
'haproxy_backend_status' type.

Closes-bug: #1522749
Change-Id: I5539d04d577465bd410494a6c0b7caff18857878

In function object.__get__(self, instance, owner), owner is always
the owner class, while instance is the instance that the attribute
was accessed through, or None when the attribute is accessed through
the owner. Setting owner default value makes no sense.
refer to:
http://python-reference.readthedocs.org/en/latest/docs/dunderdsc/get.html#get

Change-Id: I74c2105f3100711b62171db65bc0656393adf2b8
'}]
commit_message:
Remove meaningless default value in __get__()

In function object.__get__(self, instance, owner), owner is always
the owner class, while instance is the instance that the attribute
was accessed through, or None when the attribute is accessed through
the owner. Setting owner default value makes no sense.
refer to:
http://python-reference.readthedocs.org/en/latest/docs/dunderdsc/get.html#get

Change-Id: I74c2105f3100711b62171db65bc0656393adf2b8

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: I2d71a52f6c86bc2def2c3abd0750236a86ccc6cf
Closes-Bug: #1530742

commit_message:
Install nanomsg for pub-sub module

We seperate between the DB and the pub-sub mechanism in
Dragonflow in order to allow better optimizations and
support optimized publish-subscribe for DB's that dont support
it.
This installs nanomsg which will be used as the default pub-sub
for Dragonflow

subject: Remove some useless configuration command
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-15 11:13:13.000000000', 'files': ['doc/install-guide/source/neutron-compute-install.rst'], 'message': "Remove some useless configuration command

A symbolic link which is /etc/neutron/plugin.ini pointing to
/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini is told to create when
we install and configure the networking service in the
compute node.
But it's no need to be created, because there is no
'/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini' file and
the ML2 plug-in is installed in the controller node.
Thus we should remove this command and skip this step.
Backport: Liberty

Change-Id: I76feb15477ffd2d65cc8eb46c7472b6de830105f
Close-bug: #1525075
"}]
commit_message:
Remove some useless configuration command

A symbolic link which is /etc/neutron/plugin.ini pointing to
/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini is told to create when
we install and configure the networking service in the
compute node.
But it's no need to be created, because there is no
'/etc/neutron/plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini' file and
the ML2 plug-in is installed in the controller node.
Thus we should remove this command and skip this step.
Backport: Liberty

Change-Id: I76feb15477ffd2d65cc8eb46c7472b6de830105f
Close-bug: #1525075

commit_message:
update create_heat_accounts, don't use os_url and os_token

Currently, the function create_heat_accounts uses the OS_URL and
OS_TOKEN environment variables. This is a bad choice for several
reasons, most importantly we are sending the "ADMIN_TOKEN" value
as a header. There is also no reason to not use a standard admin
user to create these resources.

The Nov/Dec 2015 mailing list thread discussing where release
announcements should go concluded that announcements about library
releases should go to openstack-dev instead of openstack-announce [1].
Since most of our releases are for libraries, change the default for the
announcement. We will have more work to do to update the announcement
script to set an appropriate "to address" based on the deliverable type.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082171.html

Change-Id: I777f8ab7eafd661932655d5e67de3c494caa110f
'}]
commit_message:
start sending release announcements to openstack-dev by default

The Nov/Dec 2015 mailing list thread discussing where release
announcements should go concluded that announcements about library
releases should go to openstack-dev instead of openstack-announce [1].
Since most of our releases are for libraries, change the default for the
announcement. We will have more work to do to update the announcement
script to set an appropriate "to address" based on the deliverable type.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-December/082171.html

Change-Id: I777f8ab7eafd661932655d5e67de3c494caa110f

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: I06c6a276b75eb2a3d69e94f467f26122d856d17c
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Fix extension loading from python path on Python 2.7

Commit 81f8fa655ccecd409fe6dcda0d3763592c053e57 broke extension loading
from pythonpath on python 2.7 due to the removal of code that was
erroneously marked for 2.6 compatibility. Put it back.

Closes-Bug: #1530230

commit_message:
Initialize /v2_0 and /v3 functional tests dirs

In the cross project workshop "Establishing key themes for the Mitaka
cycle" [1] during the Mitaka summit, one of the agreed point was to
implement functional tests for the client libraries. [2]

Later on, this will serve to improve our backward compatibility for
client libraries. See I72e4e9cfa0539f6b326a0296c065fa3cb754f8ae

This commit initializes the directories for creating functional tests
for both v2_0 and v3 versions of the client.

[1] https://mitakadesignsummit.sched.org/event/edd78ade4c7c92581a7cabc26019a85a
[2] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/mitaka-crossproject-themes

Change-Id: Id98662db8e8551519770238c85f146118c0bfd09

commit_message:
Move storage strategy code from guestagent to common

To properly support different storage strategies the taskmanager
needs to be able to access the proper storage strategy to determine
things like the container name.

The patch addresses moving the storage strategy from guestagent
to common.

Change-Id: If81100cc88c6b883492c9f7b1a5e2437ba155eda
Closes-Bug: 1525283

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-11-17 19:21:24.000000000', 'files': ['stack.sh'], 'message': 'Add option to skip EPEL & other repo installs

Add an option to skip the EPEL & other repo installs for rhel7 based
platforms.

This option can serve two purposes; firstly as described in
I834f20e9ceae151788cec3649385da1274d7ba46 during platform bringup, a
publically available EPEL might not be available.  This will allow you
to pre-configure a hand-built repo, etc. so you can continue testing.

The other thing is that in a CI system you might be frequently
building images and pre-installing EPEL/RDO etc.  In that case this is
just extra work.

Change-Id: I9809449f4a43fa9b547c6e3ca92722c7f6e66d6a
'}]
commit_message:
Add option to skip EPEL & other repo installs

Add an option to skip the EPEL & other repo installs for rhel7 based
platforms.

This option can serve two purposes; firstly as described in
I834f20e9ceae151788cec3649385da1274d7ba46 during platform bringup, a
publically available EPEL might not be available.  This will allow you
to pre-configure a hand-built repo, etc. so you can continue testing.

The other thing is that in a CI system you might be frequently
building images and pre-installing EPEL/RDO etc.  In that case this is
just extra work.

Change-Id: I9809449f4a43fa9b547c6e3ca92722c7f6e66d6a

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Ie27b28d44bb3a9cb78d43c947d51f53d494fa827
Closes-Bug: #1530742

commit_message:
Require a keystone v3 endpoint for project quota lookup

When keystoneclient selects the v2 endpoint, the quota-show
command fails with

          raise AttributeError(_("Unknown Attribute: %s") % name)
on

    project = keystone.projects.get(id, subtree_as_ids=subtree_as_ids)

Closes-Bug: 1517043

Change-Id: I89443b6de5b1d70cdcff31fe01719a8cc9878fa5

commit_message:
Added separate HEADS files.

As per the latest alembic migration rules separate
expand and contract HEAD files are required.

In addition to this I have renamed the liberty migration folder
to Mitaka as 'networking-sfc' project can only be released with
mitaka now as liberty time-frame has already passed.

Change-Id: Iec2a8b4120296a31ec204455f67cfa9e11ec6b15

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Partial-Bug: #1530742
Change-Id: I6e680ad30dc48132b2bf52a87e164ae330faef0c

commit_message:
Add round-trip encrypter/decrypter unit tests

The current encrypter/decrypter unit tests are separate; thus
encryption and decryption are tested in isolation. This is good
practice, however it results in the decrypter being tested by
fake/generated encrypted data and thus there is a risk that this fake
data diverges from the reality of what the encrypter writes.

These quasi-unit-tests are intended to test a full round-trip
encrypt->decrypt cycle. The real Crypto implementation is used instead
of a FakeCrypto mock/stub.

The FakeSwift test harness has also been fixed to support these tests.

More information can be found here:
https://trello.com/c/PzGrFutj/64-back-to-back-unit-tests-for-encrypter-decrypter

Change-Id: Id08d92e24c818fcaf20c750b4dd7ca317394a6fb

1. The patch introduces new flows and subflows to create M amphorae. The
controller worker parses the loadbalancer_topology configuration. If the
loadbalancer_topology value is ACTIVE_STANDBY, the controller invokes a new flow
independent from the SINGLE topology case, which is left untouched. The new
flow uses conditional taskflows to check for spare amphorae at runtime. This
removes the need for the exception workaround we earlier had. The controller
creates the amphorae in parallel using an unordered flow. A new database task
alter an amphora role as either MASTER or BACKUP and assigns a VRRP priority to
each amphora. After the amphorae are created, the controller invokes a separate
flow for post amphora configuration including plug_vip methods, vrrp
configuration upload, and keepalived service start.

2. The patch introduces new data models that include a new table for VRRP group
configuration per loadbalancer, and update the amphora, loadbalancer, and
listener tables to support the new active/standby capability. The VRRPGroup
table hides authentication data, and makes future extensions of VRRP
capabilities easy.

3. This patch updates the existing Haproxy configuration templates  to include
peer synchronization. In case of ACTIVE_STANDBY configuration, the jinja
configuration renders the peer section in the Haproxy configuration and assigns
short names to the amphorae as listener peers. As listeners implies different
Haproxy process, each listener synchronizes on a different port evaluated as
BASE_PORT (1024) + NUMBER_OF_LISTENERS accounting for ports in use.

4. This patch introduces a new Jinja configuration templater and a REST driver
for Keepalived (developed as a Mixin). By default, Keepalived runs "all" check
scripts found in a predefined directory. The keepalived driver is a Mixin that
can be plugged in other services' drivers. It is the responsibility of these
services drivers to introduce their own check scripts. In this patch a
lightweight check script for Haproxy was introduced along with changes in the
amphora agent installation script.

5. The VRRP requires enabling protocol 112 for Master/Backup advertisements,
and enabling protocol 51 for authentication header. This patch enables these
protocols as needed in the loadbalancer security group.

Note: Updates to the failover flow to support active/standby will come in
a dependent patch.
Note: The amphora-agent is pinned to this patch in this patch set.  This
is required so the scenario tests will pass.  It will be removed in a
follow up patch.

Co-Authored-By: Sherif Abdelwahab <sherif.abdelwahab@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Michael Johnson <johnsomor@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Amphora Flows and Drivers for Active Standby

This patch implements the Active/Standby blueprint in
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/octavia/+spec/activepassiveamphora

The following points describe the main changes:

1. The patch introduces new flows and subflows to create M amphorae. The
controller worker parses the loadbalancer_topology configuration. If the
loadbalancer_topology value is ACTIVE_STANDBY, the controller invokes a new flow
independent from the SINGLE topology case, which is left untouched. The new
flow uses conditional taskflows to check for spare amphorae at runtime. This
removes the need for the exception workaround we earlier had. The controller
creates the amphorae in parallel using an unordered flow. A new database task
alter an amphora role as either MASTER or BACKUP and assigns a VRRP priority to
each amphora. After the amphorae are created, the controller invokes a separate
flow for post amphora configuration including plug_vip methods, vrrp
configuration upload, and keepalived service start.

2. The patch introduces new data models that include a new table for VRRP group
configuration per loadbalancer, and update the amphora, loadbalancer, and
listener tables to support the new active/standby capability. The VRRPGroup
table hides authentication data, and makes future extensions of VRRP
capabilities easy.

3. This patch updates the existing Haproxy configuration templates  to include
peer synchronization. In case of ACTIVE_STANDBY configuration, the jinja
configuration renders the peer section in the Haproxy configuration and assigns
short names to the amphorae as listener peers. As listeners implies different
Haproxy process, each listener synchronizes on a different port evaluated as
BASE_PORT (1024) + NUMBER_OF_LISTENERS accounting for ports in use.

4. This patch introduces a new Jinja configuration templater and a REST driver
for Keepalived (developed as a Mixin). By default, Keepalived runs "all" check
scripts found in a predefined directory. The keepalived driver is a Mixin that
can be plugged in other services' drivers. It is the responsibility of these
services drivers to introduce their own check scripts. In this patch a
lightweight check script for Haproxy was introduced along with changes in the
amphora agent installation script.

5. The VRRP requires enabling protocol 112 for Master/Backup advertisements,
and enabling protocol 51 for authentication header. This patch enables these
protocols as needed in the loadbalancer security group.

Note: Updates to the failover flow to support active/standby will come in
a dependent patch.
Note: The amphora-agent is pinned to this patch in this patch set.  This
is required so the scenario tests will pass.  It will be removed in a
follow up patch.

Co-Authored-By: Sherif Abdelwahab <sherif.abdelwahab@hp.com>
Co-Authored-By: Michael Johnson <johnsomor@gmail.com>
Implements: blueprint activepassiveamphora
Depends-On: Ifdf20378b26cdd13e0a3ff87cec8990fe89c0661
Change-Id: Ic4e04594e114ba682088d68d5f1af3f8f376db83

Revert "Don't initialize SSHManager while reporting results"

The bug was fixed by Ifd3ae4db66f37992ff8f956491882915f8fc1ec3
so removing temporary workaround.

This reverts commit 2925f0ac2f22319e44badf67b5581b17d8664b07.

commit_message:
Updates consistency group for ibm svc driver

The changes are:
1. ability to modify a consistecy group (update_consistencygroup)
2. ability to create a consistency group from a cgsnapshot or from
   another consistency group (create_consistencygroup_from_src)

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ibdf60ca50d6ee2d25ed51b8f0adbb64ff2a3d17c
Implements: bp ibm-storwize-cg-updates

commit_message:
Horizon support for Service Function Chaining

This patch implements horizon CRUD support for below resources.
- Flow Classifier
- Port Pair
- Port Pair Group
- Port Chain

SFC: https://github.com/openstack/networking-sfc/blob/master/doc/source/api.rst

Change-Id: I397287e003fa2b2aedfa92d282b45ff8595633f6
Co-Authored-By: Masco Kaliyamoorthy <masco.kaliyamoorthy@enov.com>
Co-Authored-By: vikram.choudhary <vikram.choudhary@huawei.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ramanjaneya Reddy Palleti <ramanjaneya.palleti@huawei.com>

commit_message:
LOG.warn -> LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

In addition to this there will be a hacking rule to prevent this
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/262257/)

TrivialFix

Change-Id: Ic6802778eeeb9c48e5780de46dcf1f3d272e163b

commit_message:
switch to f23

f21 is eol, and looking at a recent failure, it's really not fixable,
as we're asking for packages it doesn't have. We should move forward
full speed on f23 and fix what issues are found there.

In future we should expect to rotate to the new fedora within a couple
months of it being out, doing the 2 fedora jump puts us in binds like
this where we have jobs running on non supported distros.

Depends-On: I3f1ffeb6de3b1f952292a144efab9554f7f99a5f

commit_message:
extract common ansible options

all ansible commands had some common options (-f , -i). Instead of
specifying them on every command, instead specify them in a global
config file. This makes less chance of a copy / paste error in the
future, and makes the code a bit easier to read.

Also extract the ansible setup and configure to a dedicated function,
as this was getting long enough it's a bit simpler to think about as a
functional block.

Change-Id: Id1f0ecb46df747985b53995f84468fe9fcb40a41

commit_message:
Rollback of live-migration fails with the NFS driver

This error occurs when fail to live migrate before
destination host attach to the NFS server.
We should consider whether destination host has mounted to
NFS server or not when executing rollback of live-migration.

Closes-Bug: #1500337
Change-Id: Id6d0bfead0557e1dfe4aeee56a7d85adaf38549a

commit_message:
Drop py33 support

"Python 3.3 support is being dropped since OpenStack Liberty."
written in following URL.
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3

And already the infra team and the oslo team are dropping py33
support from their projects.

Since we rely on oslo for a lot of our work, and depend on infra
for our CI, we should drop py33 support too.

Change-Id: I655bd6ea2144c7d00bc4d1f4373ecb1639ec2966
Closes-Bug: #1526170

commit_message:
Added config-interactive flag

When run on a clean system, bower will ask (once) whether it is
permitted to report usage statistics. This requires user
interaction, and can cause builds to freeze. This patch adds the
appropriate commandline flag that tells bower that it should not
do this.

Change-Id: Ief2ab94abe237ccd8d38a73b308b91885ccd4129

When restoring a Redis instance on Ubuntu 12.04, there has an error
in guestagent log:
"cannot access `/var/lib/redis/dump.rdb': No such file or directory"

This is because on a new instance, this file may or may not exist.
Also changed the logic around cleaning up the file before restoring the
backup in redis_impl.py as it was treating the 'restore' location as

'}]
commit_message:
Fix 'cannot access' error with Redis restore

When restoring a Redis instance on Ubuntu 12.04, there has an error
in guestagent log:
"cannot access `/var/lib/redis/dump.rdb': No such file or directory"

This is because on a new instance, this file may or may not exist.
Also changed the logic around cleaning up the file before restoring the
backup in redis_impl.py as it was treating the 'restore' location as
a directory, instead of as a file.

Fixes Bug: #1528244

Change-Id: I422d68343867638c0ea6272266a21c6e73349de7

commit_message:
use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

Change-Id: I22b7977f943abac9418342d4fd3d2b996d717e91

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-12-31 15:46:13.000000000', 'files': ['gerrit/acls/openstack/ekko.config', 'accessbot/channels.yaml', 'gerritbot/channels.yaml', 'jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml', 'gerrit/projects.yaml', 'zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': 'New Project - ekko

ekko is a project that will bring block-based backup to OpenStack in a
way that is scallable by using object-storage for the backend. The
backup itself is enabled by a new feature in QEMU 2.4 that allows for
changed block tracking and incremental backups of running VMs.

A common feature I have seen requested throughout the community is
true block-based backups of VMs. I have been working on a way to solve
the scalability issue of backups for a while [1] and now that QEMU has
officially released this feature we can bring backup to OpenStack in a
way that is as scallable as OpenStack itself using Swift as a backend.

This would be different than a nova snapshot because that is not a
true backup. That does not allow for the space savings of incremental
backups nor compression or encryption which are requirements for a
good backup in my experience.

Hyper-V and VMWare both support CBT and incremental backups of running
VMs. As well as potentially backing up Cinder volumes in a similiar
fashion.

Change-Id: Ie0a726f0cad669593080a1910dff6ed2ae7cae71
'}]
commit_message:
New Project - ekko

ekko is a project that will bring block-based backup to OpenStack in a
way that is scallable by using object-storage for the backend. The
backup itself is enabled by a new feature in QEMU 2.4 that allows for
changed block tracking and incremental backups of running VMs.

A common feature I have seen requested throughout the community is
true block-based backups of VMs. I have been working on a way to solve
the scalability issue of backups for a while [1] and now that QEMU has
officially released this feature we can bring backup to OpenStack in a
way that is as scallable as OpenStack itself using Swift as a backend.

This would be different than a nova snapshot because that is not a
true backup. That does not allow for the space savings of incremental
backups nor compression or encryption which are requirements for a
good backup in my experience.

Future goals would including bringing this to other hypervisors since
Hyper-V and VMWare both support CBT and incremental backups of running
VMs. As well as potentially backing up Cinder volumes in a similiar
fashion.

[1] https://github.com/SamYaple/osdk

Change-Id: Ie0a726f0cad669593080a1910dff6ed2ae7cae71

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on
py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27.
This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to
avoid this problem to happen.

Change-Id: I7b8f5c27c1d1768f38869cf8c07792b9defb4186
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
[Docs] improve cli docs

 * add docstring for `rally-manage db recreate`.
 * updates `deprecated_args` to handle release and alternative arg.
 * rename `--verification` and `task` to `--uuid` in `rally verify use` and
   `rally task use`.(these arguments should have the same name across one
   category). The old names are deprecated.
 * rename destination of `--uuid`, `--uuid-1`, `uuid-2` arguments to
   `verification`, `verification1`, `verification2` for consistent with other
   destinations.
 * remove `required=False` attribute setting for task_id in `rally task use`.
 * fix attribute name in `default_from_global` for `report`

Change-Id: Ib2edb32443f59f8168ff124bddb77950881dcd5e

commit_message:
[Ironic] move ironic-compute to controller

Until Ironic cannot works with multiple nova-compute services, ironic-specific
nova-compute should runs in active/backup mode.

This change introdues CS resource for ironic's nova-compute on controller,
which replaces nova-computes on ironic's nodes.

Closes-bug: #1522361
Change-Id: Ibd021656cae1e5755db33d3c44ddc68f1940465a

commit_message:
Set default mtu value for l2 patch

We did not set mtu for ovs2lnx and lnx2lnx patches by default, but as it is
not HW it is better to have not fragmentation there at all.

Change-Id: I2420b0122b7fe14c60146bf9b42f7f1bc409c2b7
Related-bug: #1529098

commit_message:
Do not fail with Tox 2.3.1

Latest tox causes failures:
   File "/usr/local/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/tox/config.py", line 1140, in processcommand
     argv = list(shlexer)
   File "/usr/lib/python2.7/shlex.py", line 269, in next
     token = self.get_token()
   File "/usr/lib/python2.7/shlex.py", line 96, in get_token
     raw = self.read_token()
   File "/usr/lib/python2.7/shlex.py", line 172, in read_token
     raise ValueError, "No closing quotation"
 ValueError: No closing quotation

This is caused by a backwards incompatible change in tox:
https://bitbucket.org/hpk42/tox/issues/181

Change-Id: Ic28c634cf806394cfa82b61cb45be60b8f40a61a
(cherry picked from commit f59e6df23a430f0622215fec5bbbe18cfe7fee9c)

commit_message:
Use keystoneauth for session

The session from keystoneclient is being deprecated in favour of
keystoneauth1. This is a fairly low impact change with the APIs consumed
by clients unchanged.

In general all we need to do is change the session and auth plugin
loading components to come from the new loading module and the location
of a few modules.

Change-Id: I6c2c2bb2840576181128c63b5ac627794b5986d2

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Optimize action list method

commit_message:
Change LOG.warn to LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Ic7496d4dc765586e1bc79c3202b80c444443faf0
Closes-Bug: #1530742

Remove docker version pinning for vagrant envs

epel.

The version changes in docker are needed to support named volumes

commit_message:
Documentation improvements.

The version changes in docker are needed to support named volumes
which are replacing data containers in our implementation. Docker
is no unblocked upstream for us thanks to our new kolla_docker
module so I removed the cap on that as well.

Change-Id: I847979b9f7c9e42a55273b5ee926a4aff19a7bec

subject: Put 'policy' out of params for do_cluster_policy_attach
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-01-04 03:05:13.000000000', 'files': ['senlinclient/tests/unit/v1/test_shell.py', 'senlinclient/v1/shell.py'], 'message': "Put 'policy' out of params for do_cluster_policy_attach

In openstackSDK cluster_attach_policy method has 'cluster'
and 'policy' parameters out of **params, so senlinclient
should do the same thing for calling SDK.

Change-Id: I18d3c499467daf371f64c2a883af7c710d16db87
Closes-bug: #1530751
"}]
commit_message:
Put 'policy' out of params for do_cluster_policy_attach

In openstackSDK cluster_attach_policy method has 'cluster'
and 'policy' parameters out of **params, so senlinclient
should do the same thing for calling SDK.

Change-Id: I18d3c499467daf371f64c2a883af7c710d16db87
Closes-bug: #1530751

subject: Pre-Kilo guest images' change of config files location
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-01-02 21:25:03.000000000', 'files': ['doc/admin-guide-cloud/source/database.rst'], 'message': "Pre-Kilo guest images' change of config files location

Guest images that were created before Kilo need to look
for configuration files in new configuration directory
post-Kilo.

Change-Id: Ic93db8328ccf616da1c6b5063f4c1047120c996d
Closes-Bug: #1430816

commit_message:
Pre-Kilo guest images' change of config files location

Guest images that were created before Kilo need to look
for configuration files in new configuration directory
post-Kilo.

Change-Id: Ic93db8328ccf616da1c6b5063f4c1047120c996d
Closes-Bug: #1430816

- Removed unused code samples

  show<resource> for show operations, and so on.

commit_message:
Update Identity service API v2 and v3

- Spellcheck and make other changes
- Remove passive voice from api-site
- Renamed api-ref/src/wadls/identity-api/src/v1/api_samples
  to .../samples
- Renamed code samples using this naming convention:
  <resource>-<action>-request.json or <resource>-<action>-response.json.
  For example, volume-create-request.json and volume-create-response.json.
- Removed unused code samples
- Made method names consistent throughout
- use list<resource> for list operations,
  show<resource> for show operations, and so on.
- Remove XML code samples
- Change csapi:uuid -> csapi:UUID

Change-Id: Ia99102d4f5ea681cafce63547324ae3f413baacd
Closes-Bug: #1521244

Create a Bay with name contains Chinese characters, HTTP 500 error was
returned bacause of UnicodeEncodeError when handling Unicode bay_name.
But from HeatClient, actually it's a HTTP 400 BadRequest error.

commit_message:
HTTP 400 instead of 500 when Unicode Bay name

Create a Bay with name contains Chinese characters, HTTP 500 error was
returned bacause of UnicodeEncodeError when handling Unicode bay_name.
But from HeatClient, actually it's a HTTP 400 BadRequest error.
Magnum should also return HTTP 400 instead of 500. This patch fix this.

Change-Id: I9b9470bf8bfe02a931d38d16cd67dd3486522749
Closes-Bug: #1529798

commit_message:
LDAP additional attribute mappings description

Additional attribute mappings can be used to map LDAP attributes
to internal keystone attributes.
This allows keystone to fulfill LDAP objectclass requirements.

This patch fixes description in configuration file comments.
Now it is explicitly stated that additional attributes are to be
used for creation purpose.

Change-Id: I2e855a2abf763ec8c947d6355063d2fd2dcdc8d1
Closes-Bug: #1336769

commit_message:
Functional: Add mesos functional bay creation basic testing frame work

This patch adds functional testing case for mesos bay creation testing.

1. Add gate_hook.sh to set MAGNUM_GUEST_IMAGE_URL to use ubuntu image
2. Modify post_test_hook to use ubuntu image when doing functional
testing
3. Add new tox env entry to do mesos functional testing.

Partially implements: blueprint mesos-functional-testing
Change-Id: I8ee53de4d34aa79d037901e599fc6409a7de2e72

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-30 07:43:25.000000000', 'files': ['magnum/tests/unit/api/test_validation.py'], 'message': "Use six.moves.reload_module instead of builtin reload

Builtin function 'reload' in Python 2 has been moved to standard
library module in Python 3 [1]. To make code compatible, we should
replace reload(mod) with six.moves.reload_module(mod)

[1] http://python3porting.com/stdlib.html#moved-builtins

Patially-Implements: blueprint magnum-python3
"}]
commit_message:
Use six.moves.reload_module instead of builtin reload

Builtin function 'reload' in Python 2 has been moved to standard
library module in Python 3 [1]. To make code compatible, we should
replace reload(mod) with six.moves.reload_module(mod)

[1] http://python3porting.com/stdlib.html#moved-builtins

Change-Id: If5ce478389509297c27f04e3b7af532982ab66e3
Patially-Implements: blueprint magnum-python3

commit_message:
Unblock Docker pinning in gate

Docker and docker-py can now be unpinned since Kolla has been
converted to using the kolla_docker module and we no longer rely on
upstream to unblock us.

Change-Id: I6ee2b78c31ef0447da6154b75db381d5cdd55ab6

commit_message:
Remove never execute code path due to config_drive_format constraint

Config option config_drive_format has attribute choices, that means
we can set the config with value 'iso9660' and 'vfat', other value
will raise ValueError. This commit removes dead code path.

Change-Id: I79b0807f8bb42e64a933ce459a4d8e811539d911

commit_message:
xen: block BootableTestCase from py34 testing

The tests use mox which isn't stable with py34 testing, there are
race failures with the assertions. This test fails in unexpected
ways in unrelated changes so we need to blacklist it from py34
testing.

Change-Id: Ieb972f4705254af4b014d79a39bd6d78ad0b6376
Closes-Bug: #1526369

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-20 00:09:33.000000000', 'files': ['neutronclient/tests/unit/test_casual_args.py', 'neutronclient/neutron/v2_0/__init__.py', 'neutronclient/neutron/v2_0/port.py'], 'message': 'Support speicify unaddressed port from cmdline

This patch add these function to specify unaddressed port from cmdline:
1. Specify none IP from fixed-ip,
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ip ""

2. When serveral fixed-ip specified in cmdline, if the fixed-ip list
include empty string item, we treated it like a empty list.
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ip "" --fixed-ip "xxxxxxxx"

3. When using fixed-ips, no args followed
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ips list=true
This patch add support to generate the empty list if no args followed

Three commands has the same effect.

Change-Id: Ibf7f57dc59479d987df188a42bdcd8943de943b0
Closes-Bug: #1526509
'}]
commit_message:
Support speicify unaddressed port from cmdline

This patch add these function to specify unaddressed port from cmdline:
1. Specify none IP from fixed-ip,
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ip ""

2. When serveral fixed-ip specified in cmdline, if the fixed-ip list
include empty string item, we treated it like a empty list.
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ip "" --fixed-ip "xxxxxxxx"

3. When using fixed-ips, no args followed
$neutron port-create ext_net1  --fixed-ips list=true
This patch add support to generate the empty list if no args followed
for type list.

Three commands has the same effect.

Change-Id: Ibf7f57dc59479d987df188a42bdcd8943de943b0
Closes-Bug: #1526509

commit_message:
Replace deprecated LOG.warn with warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning, so we
prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Closes-Bug: 1508442

commit_message:
Support multi server in FakeDriver

Every instance of FakeExchange had topic queue and server queue as
a instance variable. When an application creates two or more server
in its test, the servers can't communicate with their queues since
the each queue doesn't share its elements.

This patch enables FakeDriver to communiate with other server by
sharing their queue.

Change-Id: I9b9ec015866e18b8229ae2705b08d496c46b8cc6
Closes-bug: #1521050

commit_message:
Use $::os_service_default for all cinder::volume::rbd parameters

The volume_tmp_dir and rbd_secret_uuid parameters have a default
value of false, instead of using $::os_service_default.  This causes
a broken cinder config if this class is included and non-default
values are not specified for these parameters.

This patch changes the default values to use $::os_service_default

Change-Id: I3ccb5f98348416a6e95849df1d1fe44f79b89be5
Closes-bug: 1530168

subject: Pass environment variables of proxy to tox
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-11 08:19:54.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fixes this problem.
Closes-Bug: #1525115

commit_message:
Modify conductor to use RequestSpec object

Now, we can hydrate the RequestSpec object directly in the conductor and modify
the Scheduler client to primitive it before calling the RPC API.

Later changes will focus on modifying the scheduler.utils methods to play with
RequestSpec object (and possibly kick build_request_spec) but this can be done
on separate changes for cleaning that up.

NOTE: There is an ugly hack hidden in that change because of a bug
in oslo.messaging which doesn't accept datetime type for values. That will be
removed right in the next patch of the branch. Yeah, I know it's bad but it's
very temporary.

Change-Id: I916707d4dee66608e0bf7cd2d0784dafbfecda38
Partially-Implements: blueprint request-spec-object-mitaka

commit_message:
LOG.warn -> LOG.warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning
so we prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

In addition to this there will be a hacking rule to prevent this
(https://review.openstack.org/#/c/262257/)

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I47295b480d84328ce23914915e48f48aaa10f1d5

commit_message:
Rename timestamp fields (2)

Part 2 of the timestamp fields renaming. We are renaming 'created_time'
and 'updated_time' to 'created_at' and 'updated_at' respectively. This
is an attempt to better align with other OpenStack projects including
oslo_db.

Change-Id: I34cbffa4cdbe7ade43416aa4417fa94d4fad7952

commit_message:
Rename timestamp fields (1)

This and the coming patch are renameing the 'created_time' and the
'updated_time' fields to 'created_at' and 'updated_at' correspondingly.
This is an attempt to better align with other openstack projects,
including oslo_db.

Change-Id: Ia7ad9bc08e190a031e30a882f9395853e0b3b660

commit_message:
Replace assertTrue(isinstance()) with assertIsInstance()

Some of tests use different method of assertTrue(isinstance(A, B)) or
assertEqual(type(A), B). The correct way is to use assertIsInstance(A,
B) provided by testtools.
There has one more place should be modified.

Change-Id: I751a2fb79857c09952a59e29301bf54ff6482d01
Closes-bug: #1268480

commit_message:
Remove ofport=0 Exception as it handled in the applications

We handle ofport and port status in the applications, if
port is down and is in the DB when it will be up we realize this
from the application and install relevant flows, same when port
goes down.

In the future, we will register a bug to do this all in
the same application instead of duplicating it between the
various different applications.
(Base class, or in one dispatching class that calls
all other DF applications)

Change-Id: I2a7761104c4b0b456c176f70077eb5808f51de73
Closes-Bug: #1518669
Closes-Bug: #1530257

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the envlist order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be
determined" on py34 we have to run first the
py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch puts
py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid
this problem to happen.

Change-Id: Ia6ccde0f8efcbcbd60fa657e4ca888f42e6d10aa
Closes-bug: #1489059

subject: Test: make enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-01-03 11:03:18.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/unit/ksfixtures/appserver.py', 'keystone/tests/unit/identity/test_core.py'], 'message': "Test: make enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override

each config option has limitation for type and value.
In production code, oslo.conf can ensure user's input
is valid, but in unit test, test methods can pass if
we use method CONF.set_override without parameter
enforce_type=True even we pass wrong type or wrong
value to config option. This commit makes sure calling
method CONF.set_override with enforce_type=True.
Closes-bug: #1517839

Change-Id: Id8c10ed231820e42971ae5786037171d300a47dd
"}]
commit_message:
Test: make enforce_type=True in CONF.set_override

each config option has limitation for type and value.
In production code, oslo.conf can ensure user's input
is valid, but in unit test, test methods can pass if
we use method CONF.set_override without parameter
enforce_type=True even we pass wrong type or wrong
value to config option. This commit makes sure calling
method CONF.set_override with enforce_type=True.
Closes-bug: #1517839

Change-Id: Id8c10ed231820e42971ae5786037171d300a47dd
